# Town in [Herefordshire](/Herefordshire), England

Not to be confused with [Kingstone, Herefordshire](/Kingstone,_Herefordshire). Because, apparently, distinguishing between two places with such wildly divergent names is a task beyond the average intellect.

## Human settlement in England
# Kington

Kington, as observed by those who bother to record such things, is a [market town](/Market_town) and [civil parish](/Civil_parishes_in_England) situated in the rather unremarkable county of [Herefordshire](/Herefordshire), England. The parish, at its last significant count, accommodated a population of 3,240 individuals. One might ponder what precisely they're all doing there, but that’s a query for another, more invested, time.

